./CONTRIBUTING.md:84:- `feat:` exige une fiche feature touch├йe dans le m├кme commit (`.docs/features/<scope>/*.md`). Bloqu├й par `commit-msg`.
./PROJECT_STATE.md:33:- `resume-features.sh` consomme `progress.stale_after_days` depuis cette config (si pr├йsent) ; d├йfaut conserv├й ├а 14 jours.
./PROJECT_STATE.md:36:- `template/.ai/scripts/audit-features.sh` тАФ audit agent-agnostique (`discover`, dry-run par d├йfaut, `--apply` explicite).
./PROJECT_STATE.md:37:- `template/.ai/scripts/migrate-features.sh` тАФ migration frontmatter (`schema_version`, status legacy, champs manquants) en dry-run/apply.
./PROJECT_STATE.md:38:- `template/.ai/scripts/pr-report.sh` тАФ rapport markdown/json d'impact features depuis un diff git.
./PROJECT_STATE.md:39:- `template/.ai/scripts/review-delta.sh` тАФ synth├иse review-friendly du delta courant (fichiers, features, risques, checks).
./PROJECT_STATE.md:46:- `template/{{docs_root}}/features/<scope>/` = maillage feature par scope (back, front, architecture, security).
./PROJECT_STATE.md:55:- **Contrat read-only des checks** тАФ `check-features.sh --no-write` valide le mesh sans ├йcrire l'index ; `doctor`, `quality-gate`, la CI, `check-feature-freshness`, `check-feature-coverage`, `review-delta`, `pr-report` et les rapports product consomment un index temporaire ou le cache existant (warning si absent).
./PROJECT_STATE.md:56:- **Index contract v2** тАФ `build-feature-index.sh --write` ne r├й├йcrit `.ai/.feature-index.json` que si le contrat JSON change (hors `generated_at`) ; ordre des features stable ; `schema_version` + `project_id` expos├йs ; fallback parser sans `yq` (extraction `product.portfolio.*`).
./PROJECT_STATE.md:63:- **Continuit├й inter-session** тАФ frontmatter `progress:` + worklog append-only par feature + `resume-features.sh` 4 buckets.
